tting them be subject to a roller coaster treatment, then obviously I&#39;m subjecting them to nontrivial physical effects that influence balance. However, if I&#39;m not doing any better than alternative treatments where they are not subject to such influences, then I can&#39;t say that the roller coaster had any effect on the vertigo. My theory may well be very plausible, there may exist experimentally confirmed mechanisms that support my theory. But it&#39;s then all irrelevant."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef69e4c7ba6adf44fc3d17c4bbacec01?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":10401,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10401/tanmath","reputation":1620,"display_name":"TanMath","accept_rate":58},"score":0,"post_id":39983,"edited":false,"creation_date":1445990228,"comment_id":67142,"body":"@inf3rno says that your video wasn&#39;t about whether acupuncture works... Maybe another link about placebo and acupuncture is better?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/861af9d6f7fed014708d7cc880259b46?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":8202,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8202/count-iblis","reputation":266,"display_name":"Count Iblis"},"score":0,"post_id":39983,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef69e4c7ba6adf44fc3d17c4bbacec01?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":10401,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10401/tanmath","reputation":1620,"display_name":"TanMath","accept_rate":58},"edited":false,"creation_date":1445990612,"comment_id":67143,"body":"If you watch the entire video, you&#39;ll see sham acupuncture with patients discussing complaints compared to real acupuncture."}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1445918722,"creation_date":1445918722,"body":"<p>It works via the placebo effect which according to recent research, is <a href=\"http://www.dailymotion.com/video/