aves.<\/p>\n","answer_id":34723,"question_id":34681,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/34681/is-there-a-consensus-on-the-camv-35s-minimal-promoter-sequence","last_activity_date":1445959128,"creation_date":1432886153,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is there a consensus on the CaMV 35S minimal promoter sequence?","body":"<p>We have an algal enhancer element and a transcription factor that probably binds it. Basal expression of the enhancer element or full promoter driving luciferase in tobacco protoplast was extremely low. I heard this could be overcome by fusing it to a minimal 35S promoter fragment but I can't seem to find a clear sequence for this minimal promoter.The best I could find was on the cambia website where they say it is -90 <a href=\"http://www.cambia.org/daisy/promoters/242/g1/250/264.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.cambia.org/daisy/promoters/242/g1/250/264.html<\/a> <\/p>\n\n<p>1) Does anybody have experience with increasing the expression of enhancer elements like this? \n2) And what sequence did you use for this?<\/p>\n","question_id":34681,"tags":["gene-expression","transcription-factor"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":145,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1432909491},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/34142aa2339539062f8e7b5dd1405702?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19648,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19648/alvin","reputation":1,"display_name":"alvin"},"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39994/what-is-the-natural-way-of-rose-to-propagate-by-its-vegetative-cells","last_activity_date":1445958326,"creation_date":1445958326,"answer_count":0,"title":"what is the natural way of rose to propagate by its vegetative cells?","body":"<p>I have read that rose reproduces sexually. But I have also heard that it can propagate by its vegetative cells (vegetative cells in its root). Is this correct? If yes, can I kn